Frequently Asked Question


CLIENTS

   What is Team Envy Gaming ?
Extended Reality Team Envy Gaming is a software solution that enables influential brands to elevate their level of engagement with their existing community of fans/supporters by integrating a gaming & esports ecosystem.
   How does it work?
Team Envy Gaming is easy to use. We build a custom, private labeled community gaming platform for your fans to enjoy. Once your platform is live, you can schedule gaming events every week or every hour for your fans to enjoy.
   What does private labeled mean?
Private labeled means that your brand remains front and center for your community to engage with. Team Envy Gaming logo does not appear any where on your site. Powered by Team Envy is not a phrase shown on your gaming portal, ever. Your fans/members continue to engage with your brand, only.
   How long does it take to build my gaming platform?
Depending on your requested design, development of your gaming platform normally takes 4 to 6 weeks to rollout.
   Why do I need Team Envy Gaming as a part of my community ecosystem?
- Gaming & Esports has been the fastest growing content medium on earth for the past 5 years. Similar to 10 years ago when a social media strategy was essential for every small business, today, every brand must have an esports strategy. By 2021 only the NFL will command a larger viewership than esports.
   How much does it cost to build my custom gaming platform?
We have a detailed view of pricing options here.
    What games can my users play?
We have a full list of supported games here.
    Can I use the Team Connor Gaming platform at my local event?
Absolutely! The Team Connor Gaming platform is built to enhance your community events. With Team Connor Gaming, now you have a method to stay connected with your fans/members all year long.

USERS

   How do I sign up?
You can sign up for an account by clicking here. If youre on the site check the top right corner and youll notice a Register button, give that a click and fill in the information requested.
    How do I change and/or update your email address?
Once you login to your account just head over to My Profile which is located on the left side of the website. Once there you can update your email in the General tab!
   How do I reset my password?
With access: Once you login to your account just head over to My Profile which is located on the left side of the website. Once there you can update your password in the General tab!
Without access: Click the login button located at the top right of the website. At the bottom of the popup prompt youll see Forgot Password, give that a click and fill in the information.
   I dont have access to the email address I used to create my account, what do I do?
Please contact support. You can submit a support ticket or reach out to live chat!
   I dont have access to the email address I used to create my account, what do I do?
Please contact support. You can submit a support ticket or reach out to live chat!
    How do I join a tournament or ladder?
Once you login head over to the games page and find the title that you want to compete in. Click Play and select your platform. From there youll see a list of tournaments and ladders available to you. To join youll just click on the tournament that you want to join and click on the Participants tab followed by a click quick onto Join.
   Do I need to add money to my account?
Some tournaments will require an entry fee to be able to participate, to join those youll need to have credits loaded onto your account.
   How do I add money to my account?
Once youre logged in youll see your option on the left side for Wallet. Give that a click and then youll see a button that says Add Credits, make sure to have your credit card ready to go!
   How do I get my money back that I added to my account?
Please contact support through our Submit a Ticket.
   What is considered valid proof?
Valid proof is a clear picture or video of the players in full screen that shows the rule being broken as well as the map that is played on and who is playing. If the dispute is on who won, you must send clips in from a stream. We will not view entire streams searching for the information. If you have specific questions for your situation about what Valid Proof is please get with your tournament administrator or submit a question via our Live Chat option on the Support page!
    My opponent, or myself, was disconnected from the game, what do I do?
It is the responsibility of each player to ensure that their connection is suitable for playing online. If a player gets disconnected we recommend that they communicate with their opponent to figure out a way to finish the match i.e. if the disconnection happened at half-time, the match should be completed after one half of the new game. For specific questions please contact your tournament administrator or submit a question via our Live Chat option on the Support page!
    How can I talk to a human being for support?
Navigate over to the Support page on our website. Once youre there youll see an option for Live Chat! Keep in mind that we have a lot of individuals contacting us so wait times can vary. Our Live Chat hours are: ???? - ???? Monday Sunday.
   How do I submit my scores for a match?
Once youve completed your match youll report your score on your tournament page. Head over to where you joined the tournament and on the bracket tab, from there you can click next to your name on the bracket to submit your score. Make sure your opponent does this as well!
   How do I submit proof for a match?
If a match requires you to submit proof please make your way to the brackets located on the tournament page. Once there youll see an option next to the Report Score that will allow you to upload a screen shot or media.
   My match is disputed, how does this work?
If your match is disputed please be available to speak with a tournament administrator to get the matter quickly resolved. After a dispute youll be responsible for defending against whatever your opponent is claiming, be sure to have screen shots and stream clips ready to turn over to the administrator.
   Ive won a tournament / ladder, how do I get my prize and how long will it take?
For most prizes we will communicate through your account registered email. Most are paid out within a 7 day period, of course most will be paid out within 24 hours. Please be patient!
   How do I verify my account?
Log on to your email account that you used to create your account. Open the email that we sent you. Click on the link provided, if you dont see the verification email be sure to check your Junk/Spam folders.
